  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Drought affected population have access to lifesaving nutrition, safe water and hygiene services</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this multi-sector project is to provide life-saving nutrition and WASH assistance to drought-affected people in six districts of Lesotho. UNICEF will use CERF funds to screen and treat severe acute malnutrition among children and pregnant women, conduct community-based nutrition and hygiene counselling, and provide safe water access through water-trucking and rehabilitation of water systems. An estimated 150,443 people will benefit from this project, which will be implemented in six months.</narrative>
  </description>
